4:
So they've got 5 ships, 50 cannons,
and 500 people in total. These
pirates sure are loaded.
6:
Well then, how much do you intend
to pay for a skilled dancer such as
me? The great Roselia's skills don't
come cheap.
8: This is about all we've got...
11:
Hmm... This might be enough to pay
off my tab.
15: Eh, why not? I'll do it.
18:
I won't ask you the details, 'cause
they don't concern me. But from
what I can tell, you've got a bone
that needs picking, huh?
20:
You can leave it to me. Of course,
there's still the chance I could fail,
so... yeah, sorry if that happens!
22: Th-thank you! Thank you so much...
34:
You're the one they call Roselia, ain't
ya.
36: Indeed I am! How astute of you.
38:
Yes, you're that "dancer" people hire
for pocket change! Not right in the
head, you—no doubt the worst
sellsword I've ever heard of.
40: Ah, but you HAVE heard of me!
43:
You think I'm gonna let some
third-rate hitman do me and my
squad in?
44:
You've got another thing coming,
missy!
47:
Oh my, this has turned into quite the
gathering. You know I'm not giving
out autographs today, right?
49:
It turns out there's a whole load of
people out there that hate you!
51:
Soon as I mentioned your name,
they came runnin' here all on their
own!
57:
Hahaha. This way we can make a
few extra coins AND get our revenge
on you.
58:
Tell me, would you rather be shark
food? Or a bird in a cage?
61:
Hehe. Well. I might have screwed
this one up.
63:
What're you giggling at? Ain't no
way you're turning this one around
on us!
66:
No, you're right, I'm totally done for
here! No doubt about it.
69:
However... I don't have any
intentions of being caught alive, so...
74:
I suppose this is where it ends!
It was a good run while it lasted, this
little life of mine!
77:
She chose to die? How stupid can
someone be...
82:
So, you thought the girl that jumped
out could have been an ally of ours?
84:
I mean, aside from you lot, who else
would be crazy enough to do
something like that?!
87:
Is that the kind of reputation we
have now?
91:
Yeah, I'm not too happy to hear
that...
Anyway, I wonder what happened?
96:
So this is the afterlife, huh? It's a lot...
wetter than I imagined.
105:
Huh? I'm alive? Really?!
Thought for sure I was a goner after
blowing myself up like that.
114:
I was taking care of these pirates,
you see... But then they brought their
friends, and the situation got outta
control.
117:
So I figured: that's the end of the line
for me! Might as well go out with a
BANG, you know?
120:
What about you folks? What's your
business? Got a score that needs
settling here at the bottom of the
sea?
123:
We'll be leaving the rest up to you,
then.
127:
Now hold on, you can't just dump
her on us like that!
136:
Those mermen saved your life. You
were given a second chance. You'd
do well to cherish it.
139:
Yeah, you're right. I'll use this time to
think of some new moves—the
bomb bit is a classic, but it's getting
old, you know?
144:
New moves? I meant that this is a
second chance to live your life. Not
to look for new ways of getting
yourself killed!
147:
Oh.
Fair enough. I guess I'll take it easy
for the time being—at least until my
next brush with death.
152:
You were fighting with pirates,
weren't you? It might not be a good
idea to go back to the surface right
now.
156:
Yeah, they'll find me and catch me
right away. Come to think of it, I'm in
no place to be taking things easy!
160:
Stella, are you thinking what I'm
thinking?
165:
Yes.
I am Stella, the keeper of Starview
Village. I welcome you.
170:
Not gonna lie, I have no idea what
that means—I'm gonna assume you
want to be friends?
172:
I'm Roselia! I love dancing, and I'm
known to run up a tab at
restaurants! Oh, and I'm also an
assassin. Nice to meet you!
177:
I... see.
You better watch out for this one,
Stella.
179:
I know types like these. They're
reckless and got a penchant for
flirting with death.
182:
You're probably right! But any of us
could suddenly croak tomorrow.
Nothing's for sure.
186:
That's why I intend to spend
whatever time I have left doing the
things I love!
191: Another fine addition to the team.
